The idea of creating SIUT

Successful integration of Uzbekistan into the world economy requires the training of qualitatively new specialists with advanced engineering knowledge, creative thinking, skills in creating and implementing innovative technologies. The key to solving this difficult task is the radical restructuring of the existing system of training engineering personnel based on international standards of technical education.

This is what the Decree of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan No. 60, January 28, 2022, "On the Development Strategy of New Uzbekistan for 2022-2026" is aimed at, which provides for the creation of a Samarkand technological university together with leading technical universities of foreign countries.

Read more
Bakhtiyor Fazylov
Chairman of the Board of Trustees of SIUT

Our country is at a turning point of its development. It absorbs and implements the vision of President Sh. M. Mirziyoyev outlines for the formation of New Uzbekistan. And it is no coincidence that cardinal reforms in all spheres of the economic and social life in our country are widely supported by the entire people, especially young people.

The complexity of the period our country is going through and the responsible tasks facing us require from everyone not loud slogans, but concrete deeds and full dedication. My wish to future students of the University: study, dare, create for the good of our Motherland.

Yusuf Abdullayev
Rector of SIUT, Professor, Doctor of Pedagogical Sciences

The mission of SIUT is to train world-class engineering personnel, and the highest values of the entire University team are: honor, free thinking and humanism." We are convinced that Samarkand International University of Technology will take its rightful place in the intellectual life of Uzbekistan; and for young people it will become a powerful start-up on their path of life.

University Advantages

Powerful teaching staff

A powerful team of foreign teachers, specialists, trainers from leading educational and scientific and technological centers in America, Europe, Asia, Australia and South Africa.

Educational plans

Curricula, educational programs and methods that combine the pedagogical experience of the best technological universities in the world.

Experienced foreign teachers

Experienced foreign teachers, the latest teaching methods and techniques meeting international standards of teaching Western and Eastern languages (English, Japanese, Korean, etc.).

Research and production laboratories

Research and production laboratories of the University, equipped with the latest training devices and simulators.

Unique industrial base of the founder

The founder's unique industrial base, the opportunity to undergo training and production practice at world-class enterprises.

Obtaining prestigious diplomas

Obtaining "Double degree"¹ and "Double diploma"² diplomas, for a professional career in Uzbekistan and beyond.

Technology park and engineering and production cluster

Creation on the basis of SIUT of a powerful technology park and an engineering and production cluster using the potential of adjacent regions.

Advantage of location of SIUT

The successful location of the SIUT campus with developed infrastructure in a picturesque area on the banks of the Zeravshan River (opening in 2023).

All the above creates the most favorable conditions for training highly qualified Students, masters and PhD students, fluent in the latest intellectual technologies, innovations, and, of course, several foreign languages.

  • 1 Double degree enables students to obtain, after graduating from SIUT, a diploma qualifying in two related specialties of their profile.
  • 2 The Double Diploma provides an opportunity to obtain a diploma, which is recognized in the partner countries of SIUT.

On August 5, 2022, the Cooperation Agreement with Micromine Pty Ltd (Australia) was signed in Dushanbe (Tajikistan). Micromine is a global leader in the development of operational software solutions for the mining industry.
